line_1: And hills with spreading oaks imbrown'd!
line_2: Sung by a thousand echoes round;

line_1: Half prankt with Spring, with Summer half imbrown'd,
line_2: With woody Hill o'er Hill encompass'd round,

line_1: Half prankt with Spring, with Summer half imbrown'd,
line_2: Than whom a Fiend more fell is no where found.

line_1: Half prankt with Spring, with Summer half imbrown'd,
line_2: It was, I ween, a lovely Spot of Ground;
